DR. FAUCI:
<i>The two most devastating pandemics</i>

1:38:54.428 --> 1:38:55.971
<i>in the last 100 years</i>

1:38:56.305 --> 1:38:59.600
<i>are, sort of, like bookends on my career</i>
<i>and my life.</i>

1:39:04.229 --> 1:39:10.277
<i>When you're involved in a race</i>
<i>to stop a horrible disease...</i>

1:39:12.363 --> 1:39:17.117
you always feel you're not doing things
quickly enough... or well enough.

1:39:24.917 --> 1:39:29.129
<i>You know, it just reminds me so much</i>
<i>of when we were struggling</i>

1:39:29.213 --> 1:39:32.633
<i>to develop effective therapies for HIV.</i>

1:39:35.761 --> 1:39:37.972
If we had just gotten it

1:39:38.097 --> 1:39:40.975
a day earlier, a week earlier,
a month earlier...

1:39:41.684 --> 1:39:43.852
these number of people
would not have died.

1:39:55.114 --> 1:39:59.284
<i>One of the most mysterious aspects</i>
<i>of our universe</i>

1:39:59.576 --> 1:40:06.000
<i>is how viruses have transformed</i>
<i>our civilization.</i>

1:40:13.382 --> 1:40:16.427
<i>There was a Nobel Prize-winning</i>
<i>bacteriologist</i>

1:40:16.677 --> 1:40:21.432
<i>named Joshua Lederberg, who says,</i>
